news.title: Home sales in US rise 4.2% in February amid easing mortgage rates
news.para: Existing home sales rose 4.2% last month from January to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 4.26 million units, the National Association of Realtors said Thursday.

news.title: MCG to register FIRs against those who tamper with seals for illegal constructions in Gurugram
news.para: MCG issues notices to building owners prior to sealing their properties. Over the past year, MCG received numerous complaints about construction activities resuming in sealed buildings.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP urges officials to expedite property tax collection before March 31
news.para: For the 2024-25 fiscal year, BBMP established a property tax collection target of Rs 5,210 crore. Currently, Rs 4,604 crore has been collected, representing 88.4% of the target.

news.title: Mangaluru assistant commissioner issues order against illegal sand extraction
news.para: Complaints were received from the public that sand was being extracted from the land near the river without obtaining a licence from the mines and geology department.

news.title: Maharashtra government to deploy drones to monitor illegal mining : Revenue minister
news.para: Bawankule acknowledged that government investigations have uncovered extensive illegal mining in districts like Pune, Solapur, and Sangli, where major corporations have transgressed permitted excavation levels.

news.title: Nashik civic body chief approves offline submission of building plans till March 26
news.para: The decision was made due to a technical issue that caused the server to go down, disrupting online submissions and the approval of building plan proposals.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 1,970 properties of tax defaulters in the West Zone
news.para: In the North West Zone, 388 properties of tax defaulters were sealed, resulting in a collection of Rs 1.28 crore in property tax in a day. In the South West Zone, 308 properties of tax defaulters were sealed.

news.title: ECoR plans to transform Bhubaneswar's new railway station with high-rise towers
news.para: The ambitious project, estimated at Rs 250 crore, aims to tap into the station's significant development potential. The plan for this major infrastructure upgrade was discussed during a key meeting between railway authorities and state govt officials on March 11.

news.title: Calcutta HC questions Dinhata municipality over 'development fund' charge in PMAY applications
news.para: The court also found that the municipality struck off the names of 187 prospective beneficiaries from the PMAY list for not paying the "development fund". The name of a person from the SC community was also dropped from the list.

news.title: Hermes Distillery acquires ten residential units in Mumbai for 199.35 crore
news.para: The carpet area of each apartment is 2,482 sq ft (~230.58 sq meters), while the built-up area is 2,565 sq ft (~238.3 sq meters). The transaction value per unit ranges from Rs 19.39 crore to R 20.54 crore, with the total transaction cost amounting to Rs 199.34 crore.

news.title: Aurum Analytica reports strong growth in 2024, unveils vision for 2025
news.para: Prakash Tejwani, CEO of Aurum Analytica said, "2024 has been a transformative year for us. We’ve witnessed substantial growth, with our revenue multiplying and our client base expanding by over 100%."

news.title: Bhopal civic body seizes multiple properties for unpaid taxes
news.para: Eight properties were initially targeted for seizure. Three owners paid outstanding amounts during the operation. BMC commissioner Harendra Narayan ordered the recovery effort and directed strict action against those with outstanding balances.

news.title: Signature Global acquires 8.38-acre land in sector 37D, Gurugram for Rs 282.42 crore
news.para: Signature Global intends to launch the project on this land parcel by the end of next financial year (2025-26) and expects total revenue of around Rs 3,200 crore.

news.title: Oberoi Realty to sell 21.74% share in I-Ven Realty to Alpha Wave Ventures for Rs 1,250 crore
news.para: I-Ven is a joint venture company of Oberoi Realty, and the shares of I-Ven are currently held between company and Vikas in equal proportion.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Shops & malls within 500 meters of metro, RRTS to pay special amenities fee now
news.para: UP govt has made provisions for the same in its UP Urban Planning and Development (Assessment, Levy, and Collection of Special Amenity Fee) Rules 2024, and a govt order (GO) in this regard was issued by the state govt.

news.title: Asian Paints completes divestment of Indonesian operations
news.para: APIPL on Thursday completed the divestment of the Indonesia operations by sale of the entire stake held by APIPL in PTAPI & PTAPCI for a consideration of SGD 6.8 million (about Rs 44 crore), Asian Paints said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Etonhurst Capital raises Rs 180 crore as first close of Mumbai redevelopment fund
news.para: The first close of the fund has witnessed participation from family offices, high-net-worth individuals (HNIs) and The Guardian Real Estate Advisory’s family office.

news.title: Online tenant verification rollout in Pune, Mumbai from next month
news.para: Registration department officials on Thursday said the integration would cover 130 police stations in Mumbai city and suburban areas, and 87 police stations in Pune city and rural areas.

news.title: Government to recognise private layout roads, seal illegal constructions in Bengaluru
news.para: “Roads have been developed in private layouts across the city. While we have also worked on their development, land records still show the original owners’ names. These records need to be updated, and private layout roads must be officially recognized as public roads,” he stated.

news.title: Nisus Finance's fund exits from Shapoorji Pallonji Real Estate's subsidiary
news.para: RESO-I had invested Rs 105 crore into senior secured rated listed non-convertible debentures (NCDs) issued by Suvita Real Estate, a subsidiary of SPRE, in January 2024.
